snippet: Britain's Andy Murray claimed a record fifth title at Queen's Club on Sunday as the top-seeded defending champion recovered from a set and 3-0 down to beat Milos Raonic 6-7 (5), 6-4, 6-3....
lead_paragraph: Britain's Andy Murray claimed a record fifth title at Queen's Club on Sunday as the top-seeded defending champion recovered from a set and 3-0 down to beat Milos Raonic 6-7 (5), 6-4, 6-3.

headline.print_headline: Murray Beats Raonic to Claim 5th Queen's Club Title
headline.main: Murray Beats Raonic to Claim 5th Queen's Club Title
